I will have vite bundle all the javascript. How do I get the server to serve it?                
                                                                                   
  Searched for 1 pattern (ctrl+o to expand)                                                       
                                                            
⏺ The mechanism is already in place — here's how the pieces connect:                              
   
  web/embed.go contains:                                                                          
  //go:embed dist                                           
  var DistFS embed.FS                                                                             
                                                            
  The //go:embed directive bakes the entire web/dist/ tree into the Go binary at compile time. The
   server then serves those files via http.FileServerFS. There is no runtime file access.         
   
  Workflow                                                                                        
                                                            
  1. Set up your Vite project inside web/                                                         
                                                            
  cd web
  npm create vite@latest .   # "." = current directory
                                                                                                  
  1. Vite's default output directory is already dist, which is exactly what //go:embed dist       
  expects. No vite.config.js changes are needed for that.                                         
  2. Build the frontend                                                                           
                                                            
  cd web && npm run build

  2. This writes the bundled output to web/dist/.                                                 
  3. Rebuild the Go server
                                                                                                  
  go build -o spacegame ./srv/cmd/spacegame                 

  3. This is the step people forget. Because the files are embedded at compile time, every time   
  you change frontend code you need to rebuild the binary. The previous web/dist/ contents
  (including the placeholder index.html) are replaced by Vite's output, and the new Go binary     
  embeds the new files.                                     
  4. Run

  ./spacegame       # from the repo root                                                          
   
  Why recompile is required                                                                       
                                                            
  //go:embed is not a runtime file server — it reads the files from disk once, at go build time,  
  and stores them in the binary. This is what makes the server self-contained (no web/dist/
  directory needed at runtime), but it means the build steps are coupled.                         
                                                            
  For development (avoid rebuilding Go on every JS change)                                        
   
  During active frontend development, rebuilding Go every time is tedious. You can swap to runtime
   file serving temporarily by changing server.go to use http.FileServer(http.Dir("web/dist"))
  instead of the embed, then switch back to the embed for production builds. That said, since the 
  API is all that the frontend calls, you can also just run vite dev (which has its own dev server
   with HMR) pointed at http://127.0.0.1:8080 for the API — Vite's proxy config in vite.config.js
  handles this:

  export default {
    server: {
      proxy: {
        '/api': 'http://127.0.0.1:8080'
      }                                                                                           
    }
  }                                                                                               
                                                            
  With that setup: npm run dev for frontend development (JS changes hot-reload instantly), go run 
  ./srv/cmd/spacegame for the API backend. When ready to ship, npm run build then go build.
 
